m the scoped remote tree.\n\n5. **Retry semantics**\n\n   Keep it boring:\n\n   ```text\n   fetch agentlog ref\n   materialize agentlog ref\n   serialize agentlog scope\n   push agentlog ref\n   if rejected: fetch/materialize/serialize/retry\n   ```\n\n   Bounded retry, no fancy conflict UI.\n\n6. **Reader defensiveness**\n\n   After sync, readers should still dedupe by `record_hash` and sort by transcript fields. We don’t need to implement the future reader now, but tests for sync should probably verify duplicate-ish remote/local data doesn’t produce an obviously broken local view.\n\n7. **Privacy wording**\n\n   Since this is the first command that sends transcripts anywhere, the command/help should be clear that it syncs redacted agentlog metadata to the remote. No giant warning wall, but not silent either.\n\nMy strongest recommendation: patch GitMeta first with a clean “sync this key scope to this local/remote ref” API, including scoped sync bookkeeping. Then `but-agentlog` can stay small and call that API. That keeps the POC aligned with [agentlog-sync-lifecycle.md]([REDACTED:entropy].md:1) without turning `but-agentlog` into Git transport code.","tool_name":null,"tool_input":null,"source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-11T16:49:50.382Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"message","role":"assistant","phase":"final_answer"}}}